WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:58.058 --> 00:01:00.261
They can't know you're here.

3
00:01:02.062 --> 00:01:04.031
Can't tell my messages boards
I got scanned.

4
00:01:04.132 --> 00:01:05.399
They'll never forgive me.

5
00:01:05.533 --> 00:01:06.899
I'll get banned
for inappropriate language.

6
00:01:06.900 --> 00:01:08.568
Again.

7
00:01:08.569 --> 00:01:10.271
Gotcha!

8
00:01:10.404 --> 00:01:11.771
I'm gonna get you.
I'm gonna get another one. too.

9
00:01:11.772 --> 00:01:13.174
I'm gonna get all of you.

10
00:01:14.041 --> 00:01:16.210
Oh. Phew.

11
00:01:17.044 --> 00:01:18.945
Okay. count of three.

12
00:01:18.946 --> 00:01:20.748
favorite shoe insert.

13
00:01:20.848 --> 00:01:22.015
One. two. three.

14
00:01:22.116 --> 00:01:23.250
- Orthotics.
-Orthotics.

15
00:01:23.251 --> 00:01:24.452
So true.

16
00:01:24.552 --> 00:01:26.720
Favorite candle scent.
One. two. three.

17
00:01:26.820 --> 00:01:28.622
- Papaya Sunrise.
- Papaya Sunrise.

18
00:01:28.722 --> 00:01:31.892
But what about favorite
final seasoning flourish. eh?

19
00:01:31.992 --> 00:01:33.294
One. two. three.

20
00:01:33.394 --> 00:01:34.595
- Flakey Salt.
-Au naturel.

21
00:01:34.695 --> 00:01:35.929
What? Nothing? Come on.

22
00:01:36.029 --> 00:01:37.398
Blows out your palette.

23
00:01:37.498 --> 00:01:39.267
Whoa!

24
00:01:44.138 --> 00:01:45.605
-Ew. Purps.
-Oh. boy.

25
00:01:45.606 --> 00:01:47.308
Why are you wallowing in blood?

26
00:01:47.441 --> 00:01:49.277
Yeah. Why you wallowing. Purps?

27
00:01:49.410 --> 00:01:53.146
You think I decided to wallow
by sitting in a puddle of blood?

28
00:01:53.147 --> 00:01:55.883
Hmm.
Purps's got a point. Redsie.

29
00:01:55.983 --> 00:01:57.284
Fun reminder.

30
00:01:57.285 --> 00:01:58.852
MIRA assumes no liability

31
00:01:58.952 --> 00:02:01.455
for any and all cartoonish
blood puddle slip-and-falls.

32
00:02:01.555 --> 00:02:03.156
Bloodle policy's ironclad.

33
00:02:03.157 --> 00:02:04.624
Isn't anybody worried.
I don't know.

34
00:02:04.625 --> 00:02:06.260
why there's blood
outside of MedBay?

35
00:02:06.360 --> 00:02:07.528
Wait. shut up.

36
00:02:08.296 --> 00:02:11.299
Why is there blood
outside of MedBay?

37
00:02:11.399 --> 00:02:13.467
It's locked.

38
00:02:13.567 --> 00:02:15.635
-Captain to the rescue.
-Whoa!

39
00:02:15.636 --> 00:02:17.538
Damn it.

40
00:02:17.638 --> 00:02:20.841
Captain's kick.

41
00:02:24.578 --> 00:02:28.148
Wow. sucks that I'm so ripped.
huh?

42
00:02:28.249 --> 00:02:31.819
Hey. Blue. what's wrong--
you dead in there or something?

43
00:02:34.622 --> 00:02:35.789
Maybe we can see if Blue

44
00:02:35.889 --> 00:02:37.391
is okay on the MedBay camera.

45
00:02:37.491 --> 00:02:40.661
Oh. you still collect
vintage binoculars. huh?

46
00:02:42.463 --> 00:02:44.498
Hot. hot. hot...

47
00:02:44.598 --> 00:02:47.534
Hmm. Blue's in there. all right.

48
00:02:47.535 --> 00:02:49.202
But why aren't they responding?

49
00:02:49.203 --> 00:02:50.671
Yeah. and how do we get in
to find out?

50
00:02:50.771 --> 00:02:52.171
Damn. wrong turn.

51
00:02:52.172 --> 00:02:53.541
Great Caesar's Worm Farm.

52
00:02:53.674 --> 00:02:55.309
how do you fit in those vents?

53
00:02:55.409 --> 00:02:57.510
Easy. Years of scalding
hot yoga

54
00:02:57.511 --> 00:02:58.846
gave me squish bone syndrome.

55
00:02:58.979 --> 00:03:00.681
Keeps my bone limber.

56
00:03:00.814 --> 00:03:03.183
Note to self:
"get yoga syndrome."

57
00:03:03.284 --> 00:03:05.686
Yes. sir. squeezing
through those hot metal tubes

58
00:03:05.819 --> 00:03:09.156
is like the warm caress
of a perpetual adult childbirth.

59
00:03:09.257 --> 00:03:11.359
Uh. Green. Captain's tip:

60
00:03:11.459 --> 00:03:14.462
never ask Lime
anything ever again.

61
00:03:14.562 --> 00:03:17.365
Lime. uh. can you access
MedBay using the vents?

62
00:03:17.498 --> 00:03:20.200
Can a chemtrail do a backflip?

63
00:03:20.301 --> 00:03:23.170
I'll take that as a yes.
which is profoundly kind of me.

64
00:03:23.271 --> 00:03:26.707
But we all know Lime is.
uh. navigationally challenged.

65
00:03:26.840 --> 00:03:29.577
True. Purple's idea sucks.
New plan.

66
00:03:29.677 --> 00:03:31.379
I'll guide Lime through
the vents into MedBay

67
00:03:31.479 --> 00:03:33.914
using my impeccable
sense of direction.

68
00:03:34.014 --> 00:03:35.649
And these blueprints.

69
00:03:35.749 --> 00:03:38.018
Left. Left.

70
00:03:38.118 --> 00:03:41.555
Another. uh...
uh. what does this say?

71
00:03:41.655 --> 00:03:44.056
I don't know.
I guess. uh. eight lefts.

72
00:03:44.057 --> 00:03:45.893
I'm blind as a bat down here.

73
00:03:46.026 --> 00:03:48.929
which. I'll have you know.
they weren't always blind.

74
00:03:49.029 --> 00:03:50.898
but made not to see.

75
00:03:52.433 --> 00:03:54.535
But in my next dream.
I was on a roller coaster.

76
00:03:54.635 --> 00:03:56.970
which my ThetaHealer says
symbolically represents...

77
00:03:57.070 --> 00:03:58.972
Childhood fear
of roller coasters?

78
00:03:59.072 --> 00:04:01.609
Yes. See? Now you're getting it.

79
00:04:01.742 --> 00:04:03.911
Gah. You ain't Blue.

80
00:04:04.044 --> 00:04:06.447
I mean. I'm blue-curious.

81
00:04:06.547 --> 00:04:08.882
Uh. which way is north in space?

82
00:04:08.982 --> 00:04:10.450
Uh...

83
00:04:10.451 --> 00:04:11.752
Try hanging three rights

84
00:04:11.852 --> 00:04:14.121
where Red said
to take ten lefts.

85
00:04:29.236 --> 00:04:30.538
Hi. there.

86
00:04:41.749 --> 00:04:43.817
One dead crewmate. sure.
that's an oopsie.

87
00:04:43.917 --> 00:04:47.119
But two?
Makes me look like a bad leader.

88
00:04:47.120 --> 00:04:49.156
And I can't let that happen.

89
00:04:49.256 --> 00:04:51.359
I'm afraid you already have.

90
00:04:54.428 --> 00:04:57.296
I'm a good captain.
I can't let MIRA down.

91
00:04:57.297 --> 00:04:58.632
I'm good.

92
00:04:58.732 --> 00:05:00.200
Green. mop up that bloodle.

93
00:05:00.300 --> 00:05:02.503
Orange. gather the crew
so we can tactfully tell them

94
00:05:02.603 --> 00:05:04.304
about Blue's possible
graphic death.

95
00:05:04.405 --> 00:05:06.806
Purple. rewind the footage
so we can see

96
00:05:06.807 --> 00:05:08.809
how or if Blue died.

97
00:05:08.909 --> 00:05:10.510
-Aye aye.
-Mm-hmm.

98
00:05:10.511 --> 00:05:12.813
Yeah. so. again.
the cameras can't rewind

99
00:05:12.913 --> 00:05:14.682
because they don't record.

100
00:05:14.782 --> 00:05:17.284
Well. why weren't you watching?
Isn't that your whole job?

101
00:05:17.385 --> 00:05:22.490
Uh. I had to call
my cool cousin Josh.

102
00:05:22.590 --> 00:05:23.824
Joshy.

103
00:05:23.924 --> 00:05:26.660
Make a call?
When comms are down?

104
00:05:26.760 --> 00:05:28.160
Well. I-I was practicing.

105
00:05:28.161 --> 00:05:31.298
Practicing my-my call
to my cool cousin Joshy.

106
00:05:31.399 --> 00:05:34.402
Oh. come on. I know you.
Don't lie.

107
00:05:34.502 --> 00:05:36.670
What? H-How could you even
assume I would...

108
00:05:36.804 --> 00:05:38.506
I-I mean. I-I'm not lying.

109
00:05:38.639 --> 00:05:42.042
Eh. whatever you say. Purple.

110
00:05:42.976 --> 00:05:45.178
Mm. okay.

111
00:05:52.152 --> 00:05:53.886
Yep. definitely dead.

112
00:05:53.887 --> 00:05:57.858
Even in death. Blue can make
being covered in pink goo work.

113
00:05:57.991 --> 00:05:59.527
What a legacy.

114
00:05:59.627 --> 00:06:01.862
Where's the last body scan?

115
00:06:01.962 --> 00:06:04.532
The doctor promised
to destroy mine!

116
00:06:04.632 --> 00:06:06.333
Uh. I know part
of your "process"

117
00:06:06.434 --> 00:06:07.700
is being "eccentric."

118
00:06:07.701 --> 00:06:10.037
but you can't
just trash the place.

119
00:06:10.170 --> 00:06:12.405
Weren't me.
Something sabotaged this joint

120
00:06:12.406 --> 00:06:14.041
like a government-funded
tornado.

121
00:06:14.174 --> 00:06:16.043
And that ain't
the whole parfait.

122
00:06:16.143 --> 00:06:18.979
This scan's got no bone.

123
00:06:19.079 --> 00:06:21.549
Hmm. Whose bone-less scan
is this?

124
00:06:21.649 --> 00:06:23.750
No clue. Still missing one.

125
00:06:23.751 --> 00:06:25.619
and Blue never got a chance
to label the lot of them

126
00:06:25.719 --> 00:06:29.156
before buying a one-way ticket
to the devil's playground.

127
00:06:29.256 --> 00:06:30.723
Hmm.

128
00:06:32.426 --> 00:06:34.928
No bone. Huh?

129
00:06:36.096 --> 00:06:37.097
Huh.

130
00:06:37.197 --> 00:06:38.566
No biggie.

131
00:06:38.666 --> 00:06:39.900
One of the scans is missing

132
00:06:40.033 --> 00:06:42.102
because Blue promised
to destroy yours. right?

133
00:06:42.202 --> 00:06:44.438
And the bone thing?
Probably a glitch.

134
00:06:44.538 --> 00:06:46.739
Bah. Glitches are just
big tech's way

135
00:06:46.740 --> 00:06:48.075
of gaslighting your computer.

136
00:06:48.175 --> 00:06:49.943
Uh. yeah.

137
00:06:50.043 --> 00:06:51.712
Those words are all
in a sentence.

138
00:06:51.812 --> 00:06:55.114
Now. time to tell the crew
there's another corpse on board.

139
00:07:00.253 --> 00:07:01.989
<i>
Emergency meeting.</i>

140
00:07:02.089 --> 00:07:04.291
<i>Emergency meeting.</i>

141
00:07:04.391 --> 00:07:05.726
Hi. team.

142
00:07:05.826 --> 00:07:07.795
Here to circle back
and touch base with you all.

143
00:07:07.895 --> 00:07:09.428
the captain.

144
00:07:09.429 --> 00:07:12.866
Crewmates.
A crew of mates.

145
00:07:12.966 --> 00:07:15.469
Sounds so simple.
but is it really?

146
00:07:15.603 --> 00:07:17.270
Nay.

147
00:07:17.370 --> 00:07:20.773
Alas. I am tasked with sharing
the official cause of death

148
00:07:20.774 --> 00:07:22.275
for a mate of crew.

149
00:07:22.375 --> 00:07:23.611
Try to live as they might.

150
00:07:23.744 --> 00:07:26.278
Blue officially died of...

151
00:07:26.279 --> 00:07:29.316
acute ripping off of the face.

152
00:07:34.454 --> 00:07:36.957
Oh. that was the most beautiful
part about them.

153
00:07:37.057 --> 00:07:39.492
Other than their brain.
body. shoulders.

154
00:07:39.493 --> 00:07:41.828
emotional intelligence
and depth of self.

155
00:07:41.829 --> 00:07:44.598
Yeah. now I'm stuck
looking at you ugly losers.

156
00:07:44.698 --> 00:07:45.966
No offense.

157
00:07:46.066 --> 00:07:47.166
No. you're right.

158
00:07:47.167 --> 00:07:48.301
I understand.

159
00:07:48.401 --> 00:07:50.336
Who'll be the hot one now?

160
00:07:50.337 --> 00:07:51.505
-I will.
-Yellow.

161
00:07:51.639 --> 00:07:52.940
Aw. thanks. Brown.

162
00:07:53.040 --> 00:07:54.808
No. me.
I can be the hot one now.

163
00:07:54.908 --> 00:07:57.511
Fun reminder.
Nobody's the hot one.

164
00:07:57.645 --> 00:08:00.047
We're all equally mediocre.
formless. non-sexual beings

165
00:08:00.147 --> 00:08:02.482
- who are very. very ugly.
-AW.

166
00:08:02.583 --> 00:08:04.552
Hate to steer conversation
to anything--

167
00:08:04.652 --> 00:08:06.653
I don't know--
remotely important.

168
00:08:06.654 --> 00:08:08.221
but shouldn't we be worried?

169
00:08:08.321 --> 00:08:09.823
Isn't there a murderer among us?

170
00:08:09.957 --> 00:08:11.892
Uh. no way. Two deaths?

171
00:08:11.992 --> 00:08:14.361
That's just a couple
run-of-the-mill accidents.

172
00:08:14.461 --> 00:08:16.996
Now. three makes it
a murder mystery.

173
00:08:16.997 --> 00:08:19.032
Any one of us
could be the killer.

174
00:08:19.132 --> 00:08:21.835
Maybe the roller coaster
in my dream represents...

175
00:08:21.935 --> 00:08:23.202
murder?

176
00:08:23.203 --> 00:08:25.105
Quick. Brown-- one. two. three.

177
00:08:25.205 --> 00:08:27.274
- Not a killer. Ah.
-Not a killer. Ah.

178
00:08:27.374 --> 00:08:29.176
Purple. was it you?

179
00:08:29.276 --> 00:08:31.545
Leading us to Blue
with your so-called slip?

180
00:08:31.645 --> 00:08:33.881
Hmm. "whoever smelt it
dealt it" rules.

181
00:08:34.014 --> 00:08:35.549
- Interesting.
-What?

182
00:08:35.683 --> 00:08:38.351
With that logic. it could be
Red or Green or Lime or you.

183
00:08:38.485 --> 00:08:40.788
- We all found Blue's
body together.
-True.

184
00:08:40.888 --> 00:08:43.222
And if you need me
to be the murderer.

185
00:08:43.223 --> 00:08:45.525
I'll happily take the fall
to beef up my résumé.

186
00:08:45.659 --> 00:08:46.860
No.

187
00:08:46.960 --> 00:08:48.361
Self-imposed
wrongful imprisonment

188
00:08:48.495 --> 00:08:49.797
is against company policy.

189
00:08:49.897 --> 00:08:52.065
Company-imposed wrongful
imprisonment only.

190
00:08:52.199 --> 00:08:54.334
Any decision
about who the killer is

191
00:08:54.434 --> 00:08:56.403
should be mutually agreed upon.

192
00:08:56.536 --> 00:08:58.038
No truth. no pizza.

193
00:08:58.138 --> 00:09:01.240
When the blood spills.
the marinara doesn't.

194
00:09:01.241 --> 00:09:02.541
Stop with the bad vibes.

195
00:09:02.542 --> 00:09:04.744
Solutions come
from good vibes only.

196
00:09:04.745 --> 00:09:06.413
Yes. classic scientific method:

197
00:09:06.546 --> 00:09:08.716
hypothesis. vibes. conclusion.

198
00:09:11.151 --> 00:09:13.854
Why's nobody talking
about the no-bone scan?!

199
00:09:16.423 --> 00:09:19.593
- Oh. Lime. you batty ol' coot.
-I'm younger than you!

200
00:09:19.727 --> 00:09:22.229
-Wait. you are?
-I was born
on a leap year.

201
00:09:22.329 --> 00:09:23.563
I'm only six years old.

202
00:09:23.664 --> 00:09:25.298
Ah. yes. of course you are.

203
00:09:25.398 --> 00:09:28.335
Buddy. that so-called
no-bone scan?

204
00:09:28.435 --> 00:09:31.404
It was just a glitch. remember?
Nothing nefarious.

205
00:09:31.504 --> 00:09:34.741
That's what
they want you to think.

206
00:09:34.742 --> 00:09:36.943
It's a classic UFO cover-up.

207
00:09:36.944 --> 00:09:39.713
Golly. The murderer's an alien?

208
00:09:39.813 --> 00:09:42.414
Preposterous.
Aliens aren't real.

209
00:09:42.415 --> 00:09:45.619
Yeah. kid. don't goad Lime.
They're. uh... Hmm.

210
00:09:45.753 --> 00:09:47.586
What's the polite way
to say. uh...

211
00:09:49.189 --> 00:09:52.325
Bah. The only...
I see is

212
00:09:52.425 --> 00:09:55.128
the bravado of thinking
we're the only intelligent life

213
00:09:55.262 --> 00:09:56.830
in this lonely infinity.

214
00:09:56.930 --> 00:09:58.097
Now. lean in close

215
00:09:58.098 --> 00:10:00.934
as I weave a tale
of possible truth.

216
00:10:01.034 --> 00:10:03.936
Yeah. okay.
let's cede the floor

217
00:10:03.937 --> 00:10:06.139
to the most sane member
of our crew.

218
00:10:08.942 --> 00:10:12.045
The killer's an alien
and it likes to kill

219
00:10:12.145 --> 00:10:13.781
and it looks like this.

220
00:10:13.914 --> 00:10:15.282
<i>
Hey. buddy.</i>

221
00:10:15.382 --> 00:10:16.817
-Oh. wow.
-Really?

222
00:10:16.950 --> 00:10:19.619
If this visor was an eye.
I would roll it.

223
00:10:19.720 --> 00:10:21.121
You... don't believe
I drew this?

224
00:10:21.254 --> 00:10:23.489
Oh. no. we all
believe that part.

225
00:10:23.490 --> 00:10:24.824
Mm-hmm.

226
00:10:24.825 --> 00:10:26.459
GREEN;
Okay. maybe not an alien.

227
00:10:26.593 --> 00:10:29.262
No! It's the perfect shape
to hide in bodies.

228
00:10:29.362 --> 00:10:31.431
Enough! I'm the captain.

229
00:10:31.531 --> 00:10:35.134
And I captain's promise you.
aliens aren't real.

230
00:10:35.135 --> 00:10:37.504
And even if they are.
they don't like to kill.

231
00:10:37.637 --> 00:10:39.339
None of you are safe!

232
00:10:39.472 --> 00:10:41.307
I know the truth.
I know your secrets.

233
00:10:41.308 --> 00:10:42.976
The vents whisper them to me.

234
00:10:43.110 --> 00:10:45.078
Like your little secret
in Oxygen.

235
00:10:45.178 --> 00:10:48.314
And your little book
that traps people's dreams.

236
00:10:48.315 --> 00:10:49.983
Uh. you mean my dream journal?

237
00:10:50.083 --> 00:10:53.353
Oh. c... c-clearly.
Lime's lost it. See?

238
00:10:53.486 --> 00:10:54.722
You'll all be sorry.

239
00:10:54.822 --> 00:10:56.188
When the aliens come for you

240
00:10:56.189 --> 00:10:57.824
and crawl
their little stick bodies

241
00:10:57.825 --> 00:11:00.327
inside you blobby bodies.
you'll all be sorry.

242
00:11:00.427 --> 00:11:03.563
Chaos has found a new home!

243
00:11:06.199 --> 00:11:08.668
So. clearly. the lone wolf
who went off the deep end

244
00:11:08.769 --> 00:11:10.370
is the killer. right?

245
00:11:10.470 --> 00:11:14.007
I don't know.
Lime's fear feels so traumatic.

246
00:11:14.141 --> 00:11:15.674
So real.

247
00:11:15.675 --> 00:11:17.544
So real because Lime's
afraid of us discovering

248
00:11:17.644 --> 00:11:18.846
their filthy truth?

249
00:11:18.946 --> 00:11:21.048
If I killed Blue.
I'd deny it. too.

250
00:11:21.148 --> 00:11:24.551
Hmm. of course. whoever
denied it supplied it...

251
00:11:24.651 --> 00:11:27.654
Lime is the only one of us
able to fit into the vents.

252
00:11:27.755 --> 00:11:29.823
If they could enter
to open the MedBay doors...

253
00:11:29.923 --> 00:11:31.858
They could have
also snuck in

254
00:11:31.859 --> 00:11:33.093
to kill Blue in the first place.

255
00:11:33.193 --> 00:11:34.527
But. uh. either way.

256
00:11:34.627 --> 00:11:37.330
I think we can all agree
it's a bummer to suspect

257
00:11:37.430 --> 00:11:38.665
our weird. suspicious.

258
00:11:38.766 --> 00:11:40.901
definitely-not-six-years-old
friend Lime.

259
00:11:41.001 --> 00:11:42.602
But on the flip side.

260
00:11:42.702 --> 00:11:45.537
nice to agree it's not an alien.

261
00:11:45.538 --> 00:11:47.374
The more plausible
and comforting solution

262
00:11:47.474 --> 00:11:49.142
is that it's a murderer.

263
00:11:49.242 --> 00:11:52.445
Just a regular ol' murderer.
No biggie.

264
00:11:52.545 --> 00:11:54.414
They've got guilt
written all over them.

265
00:12:02.355 --> 00:12:03.490
Hey. hey. you--

266
00:12:03.590 --> 00:12:05.258
what are doing over there?

267
00:12:05.392 --> 00:12:07.160
Oh. uh. me?

268
00:12:07.260 --> 00:12:08.695
I'm just standing here.

269
00:12:08.796 --> 00:12:10.730
No biggie.

